https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nothing\u2019s open-style headphones leak just before launch", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-23T12:46:34+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The new PlayStation 5 slim and standard PlayStation 5 standing vertically side by side on a table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/86-WrbbFmeNTswwljr_EiMMyxZk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73604709/110923_new_Playstation_5_Slim_ADiBenedetto_0010.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Antonio G. Di Benedetto / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"a7xvFD\">Get ready to see more PlayStation games. Sony is hosting a State of Play presentation tomorrow, September 24th, and <a href=\"https://blog.playstation.com/2024/09/23/state-of-play-returns-tomorrow/\">the company says</a> it will feature news and updates on \u201cmore than 20 upcoming PS5 and PS VR2 games from studios around the world.\u201d Sony says the State of Play will be more than 30 minutes long, and you\u2019ll be able to watch it at 6PM ET / 3PM PT on YouTube and Twitch. </p>\n<p id=\"3bD8dB\">The show is taking place just two days before preorders for <a href=\"h", "id": 1196937, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/23/24252281/sony-playstation-state-of-play-ps5-psvr-2-games", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "PlayStation\u2019s next State of Play will cover more than 20 PS5 and PSVR 2 games  ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-23T12:39:27+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The new smart home panel on the Google TV Streamer is coming to all Google TV devices.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tLFt1vzGKtxubh__0JrWhja1Bn0=/600x0:3840x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73604683/Smart_Home_Control_Panel_Google_TV_Streamer.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"dK8v6d\">Google announced today that it\u2019s extending all the software features of its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/23/24250684/google-tv-streamer-4k-review-smart-home-hub\">new Google TV Streamer</a> to <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/google-tv/google-tv-home-ai-sports-features/\">every Google TV device</a>. This includes its smart home control panel, a new sports page, and new Gemini-powered features. </p>\n<p id=\"7L3Pbf\">According to Google, the updates will come to all devices, including Google TVs, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21495609/google-chromecast-2020-review-streaming-remote", "id": 1196938, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/23/24252165/google-smart-home-panel-comes-to-all-google-tvs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google is bringing its smart home panel to all Google TV devices", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-23T12:39:04+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person takes a photos of lights at a street festival using an iPhone 16 Pro\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iOgz6euzBNqhvJyhCgG5bQrCQzs=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73604681/247263_iphone_16_pro_AKrales_0324.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"If3mFS\">We\u2019ve been tracking the slow redefinition of photography for years now here at <em>The Verg</em>e \u2014 I am pretty sure we kicked off the \u201cwhat is a photo\u201d debate as it relates to smartphone photography on <em>The Vergecast</em> sometime in 2018, with a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/1/20942673/google-instagram-vergecast-robby-stein-isaac-reynolds\">live show on the topic in 2019</a>. But things started changing fast this year, as more and more companies roll out AI tools that totally redefine how images are made at every step of the photography process, from <a href=\"https://www", "id": 1196939, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/23/24252231/lets-compare-apple-google-and-samsungs-definitions-of-a-photo", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Let\u2019s compare Apple, Google, and Samsung\u2019s definitions of \u2018a photo\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-23T11:13:07+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A room colorfully lit by JBL\u2019s large party speakers and lights, full of people dancing.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xPjEkSSAvpLNIKpEVuHHekUOGAY=/43x0:1158x743/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73604472/jbllights1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>JBL\u2019s party lights can sync their animations to the company\u2019s speakers.</em> | Image: JBL</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Op7Urf\">JBL has announced two new accessories for its PartyBox line of LED-enhanced Bluetooth speakers: the PartyLight Stick, which looks like a glowing animated